divs: Sighting DetailsIm not sure what this was, but it was the most beautifully colored object Iveever seen in the sky. I dont know much about astronomy, but perhaps it was ameteor or comet. I know for sure it wasnt a shooting star though. It was a lotslower, and brighter. And it wasnt even fully dark out yet. If there is ascientific explanation for this, please let me know. Thanks
Summary: shooting star looking object spoted at dusk
